snippet.textDisplay:
Not an Arsenal fan but I find myself rooting for Pepe. By the abuse he gets & the gaffes I've seen, I thought Pepe was having an abysmal year. Then I looked up Arsenal player ratings on whoscored. NICOLAS PEPE IS ARSENAL'S HIGHEST RATED PLAYER IN THE PL THIS YEAR (7.17). I couldn't believe it. Auba has 11 goals (he's at 7.10) to Pepe's 2, but Pepe is rated higher than him, Lacazette (7.12), & everybody else.


I should point out that his score is not that impressive (for instance on Chelsea Pulisic, Willian, Abraham & Alonso all score higher) but it is important relevant to the squad he's playing with. I dunno. It really surprised me. Thought Id share. YNWA fools.
snippet.textOriginal:
